rComments: J'ai adoré ce prof. Super gentil! Les leçons était claire et précise. Il faisait sur qu'on comprend et qu'on était pas stressé. Je le recommande fortement!

I quite enjoyed the format of mr. Binet's class, it was the creation of a community service project, and each week, you and your group would submit a small portion of the project. Very kind and helpful, don't hesitate to ask questions, or for clarification. No final exam, just a "analyse critique" of your project, which was simple enough to do.

This class you are expected to work hard for the Community project. You know to have développe méthode of evaluation for the Community u chose with your group. Class is some sort of mandatory because you can work on group essays for the other half of the class period. You can call in the teacher it can be a Little difficult.

He is a great teacher because he really knows what he's talking about. His exams, however, require quite some studying if you really want a good grade. They are not multiple choice, they are short and long development but if you've been following the class, you should get a good grade no problem. 2 written exams and one essay.

He is kinda scary and intimidating at first but youll lean later on that he is a real softy. Easy A. Readings are not mandatory, he assigns them but they are not part of any of the exam content. Open book exam. He basically tells you exactly what is on the exam before hand, would be hard not to get a great grade.
